i haven't downloaded this torrent yet but based on my experience with other torrents here is what you should do:
1) Mount iso to virtual drive
2) open virtual drive and run either setup or some other installation program the game has.
3) after the game is installed if you need to put in a serial you should know it or it would be in a text file packaged with the torrent. I not just wait until the game is done installing and open the virtual drive again that contains the iso.
4) unless the crack came with the iso in a separate folder, the crack will be in the iso itself in a folder labeled crack.
5) copy the contents of the crack folder into the installation directory. its usually program files, find the game you installed. lets say its borderlands, you would go to program files>Gearbox Software>Borderlands and copy the contents of the crack folder into the Borderlands folder.
6) Copy and replace everything it asks you to and then run the application.
The End. Hope This explains it clearly enough.

I got the game working on a Mac (without BootCamp or Crossover/Parallels) and configured graphics and controls, so I have no idea how some of you can't follow the instructions and use some common sense to get it working on a PC. 

This torrent works! And the graphics ARE FINE. The resolution is just set by default to 800x600, which is why it's coming out crap for you. I've changed it to 1680x1028 for my laptop but you can get it to full HD.

The No CD Crack is in the .iso file. Mount the file, look inside, you'll see a Crack folder. Use the keygen there to get a code or use one of the other codes posted in the comments here. Install the game.

Then- open the Crack folder again, take the fifa.exe file that's there and drop it into the folder Program Files > EA Sports > FIFA 2011 > Game. It'll ask if you want to replace the fifa.exe file that's already there, click yes.

As for configuring controls/graphics - I'm using a Mac so can't be sure, but I'm guessing go to:

Program Files > EA Sports > FIFA 2011 > Game > fifasetup and open fifaconfig.exe, change all you want there. Also try (in same folder) fifasetup_default.ini and change the resolution there too.
